cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a problem related to graph theory and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of parameterized complexity and the focus on algorithms make cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the most likely category. The problem also has applications in security and wireless networks, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of set systems and reductions could suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible categories.
